Bank Australia, formerly bankmecu and prior to that, the Members and Education Credit Union (mecu), is an Australian financial co-operative based in Kew, Victoria. In 2012, it reported that it had approximately 125,000 customers across Australia. The organisation employs 348 staff across Australia. Total assets were reported at A$4.32 billion, as of December 31, 2016.
On 1 September 2011, mecu Ltd became Australia's first customer owned bank, and changed its trading name to bankmecu.
On 27 July 2015, the bank announced their subsequent and final change of name, to Bank Australia, from 17 August 2015.
